{
  "log": {
    "loglevel": "warning"
  },
  "inbounds": [
    {
      "port": 443,
      "protocol": "vless",
      "settings": {
        "clients": [
          {
            "id": "REPLACE_WITH_UUID",
            "email": "user@example.com"
          }
        ],
        "decryption": "none"
      },
      "streamSettings": {
        "network": "tcp",
        "security": "reality",
        "realitySettings": {
          "show": false,
          "dest": "TARGET_DOMAIN:443",
          "serverNames": [
            "MASQUERADE_DOMAIN"
          ],
          "privateKey": "REPLACE_WITH_PRIVATE_KEY",
          "shortIds": [
            "REPLACE_WITH_SHORT_ID"
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "outbounds": [
    {
      "protocol": "freedom"
    }
  ]
}

/*
CONFIGURATION INSTRUCTIONS:

1. REPLACE_WITH_UUID: 
   Generate with: xray uuid
   Example: 71a4dd30-6d9c-4458-8153-c4ff82f6a982

2. TARGET_DOMAIN: 
   Real domain that accepts HTTPS connections
   Recommended: one.one.one.one, cloudflare.com, microsoft.com
   Must be accessible from your server

3. MASQUERADE_DOMAIN:
   Domain your traffic pretends to visit
   Should match TARGET_DOMAIN or be believable alternative
   Examples: www.microsoft.com, www.google.com, www.cloudflare.com

4. REPLACE_WITH_PRIVATE_KEY:
   Generate with: xray x25519
   Keep this secret - it's used for encryption

5. REPLACE_WITH_SHORT_ID:
   Generate random 2-8 hex characters
   Example: e70e, a1b2, f3e4d5

DEPLOYMENT NOTES:
- Save as /usr/local/etc/xray/config.json
- Restart xray: systemctl restart xray
- Check status: systemctl status xray
- View logs: journalctl -u xray -f

FIREWALL SETUP:
- Allow port 443: ufw allow 443
- Block unused ports for security

DOMAIN REQUIREMENTS:
- Point A record to your server IP
- SSL certificate not required (REALITY handles TLS)
*/